overview: The user aimed to enhance their sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage and developing an admin dashboard
  for data access. The agent evaluated the existing codebase against the SOW,
  identifying the need for a database schema, API routes for data handling, and
  an authentication-protected dashboard. A plan was formulated to use NeonDB
  (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for the database, implement API endpoints for saving
  and exporting responses (CSV), and build a simple admin dashboard.
  Authentication was initially designed with custom HMAC-signed sessions but was
  later simplified to use Next.js middleware with a basic cookie, providing a
  cleaner and more efficient way to protect routes. The agent guided the user
  through the database setup, environment variable configuration, and testing,
  ensuring all new functionalities were correctly implemented and verified.
